Richlands loop Charity Ride
description: Richlands Loop Charity Ride.  75 miles course through Onlsow County.  All proceeds will benefit The Hope for the Warriors Fund.  This ride will have a SAG Waggon with drinks and food.
course: Course is a 75 mile loop starting and ending in Richlands, NC.  Course is flat with decent roads. There will be a 1/2 mile stretch on a hard packed dirt road.
registration:
Register online http://www.bikereg.com/events/register.asp?eventid=9272

$5 late fee for day of registration
notes: Helmits are required at all times.  Rider must observe all rules of the road, this is not a closed course. USCF permit pending. All entrants are required to sign the USCF Standard Release Form at registration, wear a USCF-approved helmet, and be licensed by USCF.  Minors must have a parent or legal guardian with them when registering to sign the release form. Public racers may purchase a one-day USCF license for $10.00 on the day of the race. All USCF rules apply.
directions: From the West:   Raleigh take Hwy 70 to Kinston go right onto Hwy 258 S towards Jacksonville Richlands Parking is at the Front Parkinglot First Baptist Church 100 Rand St. Richlands NC
